snippet.title: Grateful For The Spring (Barron Trump Singing)
snippet.description:
Grateful For The Spring

Check us out on Spotify! https://open.spotify.com/album/3y1CZVxPBVqYl2ljdNVWno?si=lLRWLYbeQcuXD9TQDeKi7A

⬇️⬇️⬇️ Watch more videos below! ⬇️⬇️⬇️
https://youtu.be/WBHJZs8ZeFQ
https://youtu.be/GAdihLnAiXk
https://youtu.be/SZZW8YMZlMg?si=kP7ZE5s5fhhjjpX2
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=hq_JjAodbY0

[Verse 1]
The days were cold, the nights were long,
The world felt still, the sun was gone.
But seasons turn, and hope breaks through,
Now the skies shine clear and blue.

[Verse 2]
The frost has melted, the grass is green,
A brand-new world for me to see.
The birds are singing, the rivers run,
A gift from God, the warmth, the sun.

[Chorus]
Oh, I’m grateful for the spring,
For the life the seasons bring.
Through the dark, through the cold,
Now the light takes hold.
Every flower, every tree,
Is a sign of love to me.
Oh, I’m grateful for the spring,
And the hope it always brings.

[Verse 3]
I see the blossoms, feel the breeze,
Smell the rain upon the leaves.
It’s like a promise, whispered low,
That after storms, we bloom and grow.

[Verse 4]
Winter fades, but I still know,
Without the chill, we’d never grow.
God paints the seasons, makes them new,
And every spring, He proves it’s true.

[Chorus]
Oh, I’m grateful for the spring,
For the life the seasons bring.
Through the dark, through the cold,
Now the light takes hold.
Every flower, every tree,
Is a sign of love to me.
Oh, I’m grateful for the spring,
And the hope it always brings.

[Bridge]
Every sunrise tells a story,
Of His mercy, of His glory.
Even when the winter stays,
I know spring is on its way.

[Chorus]
Oh, I’m grateful for the spring,
For the life the seasons bring.
Through the dark, through the cold,
Now the light takes hold.
Every flower, every tree,
Is a sign of love to me.
Oh, I’m grateful for the spring,
And the hope it always brings.

[Outro]
So I’ll lift my hands and sing,
Thank You, Lord, for giving spring.
